# Context Mesh Framework

## Overview

**Context Mesh** is a framework for maintaining context in AI-assisted software development. It separates **Intent** (What/Why), **Decisions** (How), and **Knowledge** (Patterns) to ensure AI agents always work with complete context.

---

## Core Workflow (3 Steps)

| Step | Phase | Description |
|------|-------|-------------|
| 1 | **Intent** (Plan) | Define WHAT and WHY in `context/intent/` |
| 2 | **Build** (Execute) | Make technical decisions in `context/decisions/` and implement code |
| 3 | **Learn** (Reflect) | Extract patterns to `context/knowledge/` and update context |

---

## File Structure & Rules

### 1. Intent (`context/intent/`)

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `project-intent.md` | Single source of truth for project goals |
| `feature-[name].md` | One file per feature. Must link to its Decision file |

**Rules:**

- [ ] Never implement code without an Intent file
- [ ] Keep "Status" updated

---

### 2. Decisions (`context/decisions/`)

| File Pattern | Purpose |
|--------------|---------|
| `[number]-[topic].md` | Architecture Decision Records (ADR) |

**Rules:**

- [ ] Create a decision file BEFORE implementing complex features
- [ ] Link back to the Intent file (Related section)
- [ ] Must include "Context", "Decision", "Rationale", and "Alternatives"

---

### 3. Knowledge (`context/knowledge/`)

| Directory | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `patterns/[name].md` | Reusable code patterns or conventions |
| `anti-patterns/` | Approaches to avoid |

**Rules:**

- [ ] Check patterns before writing code
- [ ] If a new pattern emerges, create a file here

---

### 4. Evolution (`context/evolution/`)

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `changelog.md` | Track high-level changes to the context/project |

---

### 5. Agents (`context/agents/`)

Store prompt templates or specific agent configurations here.

---

## Operational Rules for AI Agents

### Plan, Approve, Execute

| Phase | Action |
|-------|--------|
| **Plan** | Read Intent and existing Context. Propose changes. |
| **Approve** | Wait for user confirmation. |
| **Execute** | Write code, then UPDATE the context files (Status, Outcomes). |

---

## Bidirectional Linking

### Features must link to Decisions

```markdown
- [Decision: Name](../decisions/001-name.md)
```

### Decisions must link to Features

```markdown
- [Feature: Name](../intent/feature-name.md)
```

---

## Definition of Done

- [ ] Code implemented
- [ ] Tests passed
- [ ] Context files updated (Status changed to "Completed", "Outcomes" filled in Decision)
- [ ] Changelog updated

---

## Status Section Requirements

All Intent and Decision files must end with:

```markdown
## Status

- **Created**: YYYY-MM-DD
- **Status**: [Draft/Proposed/Accepted/In Progress/Completed/Deprecated]
```

### Status Values

| Status | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `Draft` | Initial idea, not yet reviewed |
| `Proposed` | Ready for discussion |
| `Accepted` | Approved but not yet started |
| `In Progress` | Currently being implemented |
| `Completed` | Implementation finished |
| `Deprecated` | No longer valid/relevant |
